Picture this: I've recently become a DJ, and it all started with my love for electronic music, thanks to Armin Van Buuren's epic sets on "A State of Trance." When our restaurant needed a DJ, I stepped up to keep our guests grooving and give them an unforgettable experience.

The best part is, my music collection, which everyone loves, has been a treasure trove for years. I began by mixing Afro House, but as 1 dived deeper into the art, I discovered awesome new genres like Drum & Bass, Breaks, Deep House, and classic House music.

These adventures opened my mind and transformed my mixes into something truly magical! Artists like Four Tet, Stain, Sunju Hargun, and Ben UFO inspired me along the way, and though my sound keeps evolving, I'm still staying true to those infectious Afro vibes that get everyone dancing!
